The lua programming language provides a set of comparative operators. The comparative operators are used to determine equality or inequality or otherwise make comparisons of numeric or string values, and produce a boolean [[/truth/]] based on the result. In lua, all values are true, except [[/nil/]] and [[/false/]].
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Operator !! Description |- | == || [[/equality/]] |- | ~= || [[/inequality/]] |- | < || [[/lessthan/]] |- | > || [[/greaterthan/]] |- | <= || [[/less than or equal to/]] |- | >= || [[/greater than or equal to/]] |- |}
=== Coercion does not take place for comparative operators ===
print ("9" > 8) -- coercion does not take place for comparative operators
