==Resistor in parallel== Two or more resistor can be connected in paprallel to decrese the total resistance . :[[Image:Resistors_in_Series.svg|200px]] :<math>\frac{1}{R_{eq}} = \frac{1}{R_1} + \frac{1}{R_2} + ...+ \frac{1}{R_n} \,</math>
==Two equal value Resistor in parallel== When connect two reistors of the same resistance the total resistance is doubled : <math>\frac{1}{R_t} = \frac{1}{R} + \frac{1}{R} = \frac{R}{2}</math>
{{BookCat}}

==Capacitor connected in parallel== Two or more capacitors can be connected in parallel to increse the total capacitance : <math>C_t = C_1 + C_2 + .... + C_n</math>
==Two of the same value== : <math>\frac{1}{C_t} = \frac{1}{C} + \frac{1}{C} = \frac{1}{2C}</math>
{{BookCat}}

