==Microphone== A microphone is an acoustic-to-electric transducer or sensor that converts sound into an electrical signal :[[File:Mics_@_Savage_Audio.jpg|500px]]
==Construction== : [[File:US_Patent_3118022_-_Gerhard_M._Sessler_James_E._West_-_Bell_labs_-_electroacustic_transducer_-_foil_electret_condenser_microphone_1962_1964_-_pages_1-3.png|500px]]
==Reference== # [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microphone Microphone] {{Wikipedia|Microphone}}
{{BookCat}}

The graphical display window displays the object as it would appear from the [[/viewing position/]]. The [[/viewing position/]] is set according to several parameters:
* [[/centre of view/]] * [[/size of view/]] * [[/twist and angle/]] * [[/viewing angle/]]
{{BookCat}}

The grip keys are used in conjunction with the mouse or arrow keys to manipulate the [[/graphics view window/]]:
* shift - iused for translation (movement) * control - used for rotation * alt - used for constraining movement or rotation to a particular axis
{{BookCat}}

The in command is used to create new objects and insert them into the database. Note that the database must be opened before insertion can take place:
# Insert a 2 x 3 x 4 cuboid named cuboid1.s into the database in cuboid1.s rpp 0 2 0 3 0 4
{{BookCat}}

