=Diagram types=
==2D diagrams==
* parameter is a variable on horizontal axis
** bifurcation diagram : P-curves ( = periodic points) versus parameter<ref>[http://abacus.bates.edu/~sross/bifurandorbit01.html Bifurcation and Orbit Diagrams by  Chip Ross ]</ref>
** orbit diagram : points of critical orbit versus parameter 
** skeleton diagram ( [[Fractals/Iterations_in_the_complex_plane/def_cqp#Critical_curves|critical curves = q-curves]])
** Lyapunow diagram : Lyapunov exponent versus parameter
** multiplier diagrams : multiplier of periodic orbit versus parameter
* constant parameter diagrams
** cobweb diagram or a Verhulst diagram <ref>[[w:Cobweb plot|wiki : Cobweb plot]]</ref> = Graphical iteration
** Iterates versus time diagram<ref>[http://www.geom.uiuc.edu/~math5337/ds/part3/part3_trap.html One-Dimensional Dynamical Systems  Part 3: Iteration by Hinke Osinga ]</ref> = connected scatter graph = time series
** invariant density diagram , histogram <ref>[[w:histogram|wikipedia : histogram]]</ref>, the distribution of the orbit<ref>[http://theworldismysterious.wordpress.com/2013/09/30/chaos-theory-dependence-on-parameter-r-continued/ CHAOS THEORY: DEPENDENCE ON PARAMETER R  ]</ref>, frequency distribution <ref>[http://helmingstay.blogspot.com/2011/10/bat-country.html bat-country by xian]</ref> = power spectrum <ref>[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=84lq0Eh5ZX0 Power Spectrum of the Logistic Map from wolframmathematica ]</ref>


